            'Begin with three deep, grounding breaths. Feel your body making contact with the surface beneath you — chair, floor, or bed. Establish this physical sense of being held by something solid.',
            'Conduct a slow body scan from the crown of your head to the soles of your feet. Notice every area of tension, numbness, warmth, cold, tingling, heaviness, or emptiness without trying to change anything.',
            'When you find the area that holds your wound most strongly, place your hand there gently. Offer warmth and gentle pressure through your palm.',
            'Ask this body area: "What are you holding? What do you need?" Wait for the body\'s answer — it may come as sensation, image, emotion, or words.',
            'Offer your body what it needs: stillness, movement, warmth, pressure, breath, sound. Follow its guidance.',
